{"parse":{"title":"McCrone Agreement","pageid":22408251,"revid":821932188,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">This article is about the agreement involving Scottish teachers' working conditions. For the report on Scottish independence, see <a href=\"/wiki/McCrone_report\" title=\"McCrone report\">McCrone report</a>.</div>\n<p>The <b>McCrone Agreement</b> (<i>A Teaching Profession for the 21st Century: Agreement reached following recommendations made in the McCrone Report</i>) is an agreement about Scottish teachers' <a href=\"/wiki/Pay_and_conditions\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pay and conditions\">pay and conditions</a>. The agreement, under the <a href=\"/wiki/Government_of_the_1st_Scottish_Parliament\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Government of the 1st Scottish Parliament\">Labour-Liberal Democrat coalition government</a> in 2001, followed an independent committee of inquiry which reviewed teachers' pay and conditions, chaired by Professor <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Gavin_McCrone&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Gavin McCrone (page does not exist)\">Gavin McCrone</a>.\n</p><p>One of the key aims of the agreement was to ensure that teachers' <a href=\"/wiki/Workweek\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Workweek\">working weeks</a> would be limited to <a href=\"/wiki/35-hour_workweek\" title=\"35-hour workweek\">35 hours</a> though there is evidence that this has not been achieved.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=McCrone_Agreement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Education_in_Scotland\" title=\"Education in Scotland\">Education in Scotland</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=McCrone_Agreement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/scotland/2067748.stm\">Teachers say they are overworked</a> BBC NEWS, 26 June 2002</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=McCrone_Agreement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.scotland.gov.uk/Publications/2001/01/7959/File-1\">A Teaching Profession for the 21st Century: Agreement reached following recommendations made in the McCrone Report</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20090621040602/http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/research/briefings-07/SB07-03.pdf\">THE MCCRONE AGREEMENT</a> - 2007 Briefing document for the Scottish Parliament</li></ul>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Nuvola_apps_bookcase.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a5/Nuvola_apps_bookcase.svg/30px-Nuvola_apps_bookcase.svg.png\" width=\"30\" heig